  "reasoning": "The student correctly factors standard quadratics, recalls the quadratic formula, identifies a/b/c, and substitutes with correct parentheses/signs. They show a common but non-fundamental misconception/panic about a negative discriminant (domain error) rather than recognizing complex solutions, so the level should not exceed 3."
}

