  "final_level": 4,
  "reasoning": "The student correctly distinguishes ionic vs covalent bonding and accurately recalls the common GCSE shapes for methane, ammonia, and water. Their question about whether lone pairs change the molecular shape shows awareness of the electron-pair counting method, with only uncertainty about naming conventions rather than a core misconception."
}

