  "final_level": 4,
  "reasoning": "The student accurately recalls key events/dates (Bastille, Tennis Court Oath) and a major cause (Third Estate tax burden), and can apply an Enlightenment concept (popular sovereignty) to multiple phases of the revolution. They show solid understanding but still express uncertainty about explaining Rousseau’s ideas and connecting them precisely to later events, so not consistently at level 5."
}

{
  "agree": true,
  "final_level": 4,
  "reasoning": "The student correctly distinguishes analysis as cause→effect chains, gives accurate short- vs long-term examples (urban overcrowding vs middle-class growth), and recalls key points of the 1833 Factory Act, 1847 Ten Hours Act, and 1848 Public Health Act. They can generalize the short/long-term framework to strikes vs the Labour Party, though they still report difficulty applying it consistently under timed conditions."
}

{
